---
description: Do not put env/setup/credential messaging in visible product UI
alwaysApply: true
---

# No operational or setup copy in the UI

Do **not** add visible user-facing copy that explains:

- Environment variable names, API key names, or token names
- What to set in `.env`, deployment dashboards, or config to “enable” a feature
- Whether credentials are required, absent, or unnecessary
- Phrases like “runs on your machine”, “no credentials needed”, “in the browser”, “this tab”, or similar setup/privacy reassurance (unless the user explicitly asks for that copy)

This applies to titles, subtitles, body text, empty states, banners, footnotes, tooltips, and inline code in the default UI.

Operational instructions belong in **README**, **internal docs**, or comments in server-only code—not in the shipped interface.
